Chile Stocks: Cencosud, Concha & Toro, Socovesa and Vapores

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-07-04T14:56:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/chile-stocks-cencosud-concha-toro-socovesa-and-vapores.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:52 a.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell less than 0.1 percent to 4,796.43,
according to the Santiago exchange’s website.  Cencosud SA (CENCOSUD CC),  Latin America ’s third largest
retailer by sales, rose 0.3 percent to 3,335 pesos. Chilean
 consumer confidence  increased in May to 47 points from 46 in
April, Santiago-based research group Adimark GfK said in a
report on its website.  Cia. Sudamericana de Vapores SA (VAPORES CC) gained 0.4
percent to 291 pesos. Latin America’s largest container shipping
company raised more than $430 million in a rights offering of
new shares that concluded June 30, according to a July 1
statement.  Socovesa SA (SOCOVESA)   increased 1.7 percent to 305
pesos. The builder and real-estate developer plans to invest
$2.5 billion through 2015 in new projects and land acquisitions,
El Mercurio reported. The company aims to increase home sales by
about 60 percent over the same period, the newspaper reported,
citing Mauricio Varela, head of real estate.  Vina Concha & Toro SA (CONCHA CC). Chile’s largest wine
exporter, fell 1.7 percent to 1,225 pesos. The Chilean peso
strengthened for a seventh straight day, signaling lower revenue
for export-oriented companies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
